
[Slack → Claude]: the tester instructions are kinda lacking in a few areas. we need to emphasize that the tester's goal is not letting any bugs or missing functionality through. No reward is given for tests passing, just for whether the implementation actually meets the requirements. Failing tests are vastly better than passing tests that mask bugs or missing functionality. It must be strict about understanding the system-under-test (SUT) for every individual test, and never to mock anything within that system, only things _around_ it.
